# Demo Setup Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual credentials
# 2. For Supabase: Get your URL and anon key from your Supabase dashboard
# 3. For Tavus: Sign up at https://tavus.io and get your API credentials
# 4. For Airtable: Set up Pica connection and get your database/table IDs
# 5. Run the demo users migration to create sample accounts
# 6. Or manually create the demo users in your Supabase Auth dashboard:
#    - demo@example.com (Password123!)
#    - testuser@example.com (TestPass123!)
#    - john.doe@example.com (Demo123!)

# Note: The OPENAI_API_KEY and PICA_SECRET_KEY above are fallback values
# that will be used if they cannot be fetched from the database